cst/nodeTypes/Node.Node –
Node.Node.source¶

type: cst/nodeTypes/NodeTypes.ISource

An object containing the source code info of this node, including the raw text this node represents from the input stream, as well as the line/column info for the start and end of this node in the input stream.

Node.Node.toObject()¶

Returns a POJO representation of this node, while recursively providing a POJO representation for all child nodes, by calling {@link toObject} on child nodes. This is very useful for testing and debugging processes, when the entire AST needs to be easily examined.

Returns:object –
Node.Node.toString()¶

Returns the raw text associated with this node.

Returns:string – the raw text this node represents.
Node.Node.type¶

type: cst/nodeTypes/NodeTypes.NODE_TYPE

see NODE_TYPE

Attribute¶

class Attribute.Attribute()¶

exported from cst/nodeTypes/Attribute

Extends:
  • cst/nodeTypes/Node.Node()
Implements:
  • cst/nodeTypes/NodeTypes.INode()
  • cst/nodeTypes/NodeTypes.IAttribute()

An HTML attribute

Attribute.Attribute.attributeName¶

type: cst/nodeTypes/NodeTypes.AttributeName

The attribute name for this attribute. Can be either a string or a reference. If this attribute is a boolean attribute (disabled, for example), only attribute name will be set.

Attribute.Attribute.attributeValue¶

type: cst/nodeTypes/NodeTypes.AttributeValue

The attribute value for this attribute. Can be either a string, containing the surrounding attribute quotes (“foo”, for example), or a dust reference. This value will be null for boolean attributes.

Attribute.Attribute.isBooleanAttribute¶

type: boolean

Indicates if this attribute is a boolean HTML attribute. See html boolean attributes
